A cartridge (10) for use in forming a beverage, the cartridge comprising:
a container (12) defining an interior space (14) having first and second portions, the container having a surface arranged to be pierced by a piercing element to permit a beverage to exit the interior space;
a beverage medium (20) arranged to interact with liquid introduced into the container to form a beverage, the beverage medium being located in the first portion (14a) of the interior space; and
a filter (30) at least partially located in the interior space, the filter being arranged so that liquid that interacts with the beverage medium in the first portion of the interior space flows through the filter toward the second portion (14b) of the interior space;
characterized in that:
a filter guard (40) is disposed in the interior space and has a portion arranged to be contacted and displaced by a piercing element if the container surface is pierced by the piercing element to permit a beverage to exit the interior space,at least a portion of the filter is displaceable relative to the container, andthe filter guard is arranged to displace at least a portion of the filter and resist damage to the filter if at least a portion of the filter guard is displaced by contact with the piercing element.

A beverage system comprising:
a beverage machine (100) comprising:
a receptacle (120) arranged to receive a cartridge (10);
a fluid inlet (50) arranged to introduce liquid into the cartridge; and
a fluid outlet including a piercing element (52) arranged to pierce a surface of the cartridge; and
a cartridge arranged to be received by the receptacle of the beverage machine, the cartridge comprising:
a container (12) defining an interior space (14) and having the surface arranged to be pierced by a piercing element;
a beverage medium (20) in the interior space arranged to interact with liquid introduced by the fluid inlet into the container to form a beverage; and
a filter (30) at least partially located in the interior space and arranged to filter liquid that interacts with the beverage medium in the interior space;
characterized in that a filter guard (40) is arranged to be contacted and displaced by the piercing element and to displace at least a portion of the filter to resist damage to the filter if the container surface is pierced by the piercing element to permit a beverage to exit the container.

A method of making a beverage, comprising:
providing a beverage machine (100) comprising a receptacle (120) arranged to receive a cartridge, a fluid inlet (50) arranged to introduce liquid into the cartridge, and a fluid outlet including a piercing element (52) arranged to pierce a surface of the cartridge;
providing a cartridge (10) in the receptacle of the beverage machine, the cartridge including a container (12) with an interior space (14), and a filter (30) and filter guard (40) both located in the interior space and near a surface of the cartridge;
piercing the surface of the cartridge with the piercing element so as to form an opening in the surface to permit a beverage to exit the container; and
contacting the piercing element with the filter guard so as to displace a portion of the filter guard and a portion of the filter in the interior space relative to the container.

